by subtracting the lowest value (3.2 mmol/L) from the highest value (5.3 mmol/L). The range represents the spread between the extreme values in a dataset.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWhile range is an easy measure to calculate, it has limitations as a measure of spread because it only considers the two extreme values and is heavily influenced by outliers. Other measures like standard deviation or interquartile range often provide more useful information about data dispersion.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The range can be calculated by subtracting the lowest from the highest value in a dataset.","The range is sensitive to outliers and extreme values, making it less reliable than other measures of spread.","The range provides a simple measure of variability but does not indicate the distribution of values between extremes."],"references":["Sullivan LM. Essentials of biostatistics in public health. 3rd ed. Burlington (MA): Jones \u0026 Bartlett Learning; 2018.","Dawson B, Trapp RG. Basic \u0026 clinical biostatistics. 4th ed. New York: McGraw-Hill; 2004."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56146"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17445"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"56146","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/56146"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-16T13:19:32+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-16T13:20:09+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10135"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"70681"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id"